

--Available global variabes:
--	event_juggler.section - name of the config section
--	event_juggler.version - LUA plugin version

--The script must define a function handle_action(env).
--This function will be invoked by the event_juggler whenever an event occurs.
--The parameter env is a table that contains all the relevant data generated by the event.
--The contents of env will vary depending on the specific type of event, 
--so the script must be prepared to handle different data structures.
--The function handle_action(env) must return 0  to indicate that the action was handled successfully
--or a non-zero value to indicate that an error occurred.
function handle_action(env)
    --E.g the log event provides event.text, and event.type fields
    os.execute("echo '" .. env["event.text"] .. "' > /tmp/dump")

    return 0;
end
